text ~
text I was holding some luggage with both my hands as I arrived at Kotomi's house.
text White paint, thinner, varnish.
text Paint brush, wire brush, paper rasp.
text I woke up at eight in the morning and went to the paint shop to buy these.
text I told the shop owner, "I want to paint a chair in the garden," and then he thoroughly taught me how to do it and arranged the necessary things.
text Of course, I've prepared myself a change of clothes and army cotton gloves.
text I thought about this and that when I came home last night.
text And then, I decided.
text I won't hesitate anymore. I'll do everything I can.
text From now on, that's what I'm going to think; that alone has merit.
text That's what I believed.

bgload KURO.jpg 30
bgload BG051E.jpg 30

text The garden from yesterday.
text As expected, it's not possible for grass to grow thickly overnight.
text But, when I look at it with a steady eye, I can see that it was quite rough work.
text I have to think about how to do it properly if I want to make it in time for Kotomi's birthday.

bgload KURO.jpg 30
