text I move the chair and the table to the corner of the garden.
text I look at the condition of the table.
text In my memory, it was painted with a dazzling pure white.
text The coating right now is loose, and the surface is showing off some red and light brown rust here and there.
text I use the wire brush and scrape off a lump of big rust.
text The paper rasp becomes covered with fine rust.
text I smear some rust-proofing on the unprotected metal.
text I was immersing myself into working.

bgload KURO.jpg 30
bgload BG051F.jpg 45

text ~
text It took me around an hour to finish giving the table some rust-proofing.
text While letting it dry, I began working on the chair.
text I thought I was happy it was small, but its shape was so complex that it took some time.
text I did the same thing to the next chair, scraping it with a paper rasp and painting it with rust-proofing.
text I decided to trim the garden tree and the hedge before letting the chairs dry.
text I position the shears around some branches and apply some force into it.
text With a fine snapping sound, thick, lush, green leaves fell on the ground.
text I was working my way near the edge of the garden.
text ~
text @[Tomoya]
text "Whoops..."
text ~
